{"sections":[],"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Reference","anchor":"Reference","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/privacy","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/benchmark","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/release-notes","doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/CHANGELOG"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"General","type":"heading","text":"General","level":2},{"anchor":"What-is-the-difference-between-FlyHUD-FlyIndicatorHUD-and-FlyProgressHUD","type":"heading","text":"What is the difference between FlyHUD, FlyIndicatorHUD, and FlyProgressHUD?","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"FlyHUD"}]},{"text":" — The core module containing the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HUD"},{"text":" class, layout system, animations,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and background views. This is all you need for system indicators and custom views.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"FlyIndicatorHUD"}]},{"text":" — Provides custom activity indicator styles (ring clip, ball spin,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"circle stroke, arc dot). Depends on FlyHUD.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"FlyProgressHUD"}]},{"text":" — Provides custom progress view styles (bar, round, annular, pie).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Depends on FlyHUD.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"You can import only what you need. All three are independent of each other.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Why-was-it-renamed-from-LPHUD-to-FlyHUD","type":"heading","text":"Why was it renamed from LPHUD to FlyHUD?","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The library was renamed in version 1.5.6 to better reflect its nature: “Fly” implies","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"fast, efficient, and flexible — consistent with the real-time nature of a HUD.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Does-FlyHUD-support-SwiftUI","type":"heading","text":"Does FlyHUD support SwiftUI?","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes! The ","type":"text"},{"code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" module provides native SwiftUI support with declarative modifiers:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["import FlyHUDSwiftUI","","MyView()","    .hudLoading(isPresented: $isLoading, label: \"Loading...\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/flyhud.FlyHUD\/documentation\/FlyHUD\/swiftui-integration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" for complete documentation covering all API layers.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Installation","type":"heading","text":"Installation","level":2},{"anchor":"Which-module-should-I-import","type":"heading","text":"Which module should I import?","level":3},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Need"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Import"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"System spinner + custom views only"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyHUD"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"SwiftUI declarative modifiers"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyHUDSwiftUI"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom indicator animations"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyHUD"},{"type":"text","text":" + "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyIndicatorHUD"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom progress styles"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyHUD"},{"type":"text","text":" + "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"FlyProgressHUD"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All features"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All three"}]}]]]},{"anchor":"Can-I-use-only-CocoaPods-subspecs","type":"heading","text":"Can I use only CocoaPods subspecs?","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes. Use subspecs to minimize dependencies:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["pod 'FlyHUD', :subspecs => ['FlyHUD']           # Core only","pod 'FlyHUD', :subspecs => ['FlyIndicatorHUD']  # Core + indicators","pod 'FlyHUD', :subspecs => ['FlyProgressHUD']   # Core + progress"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"ruby"},{"anchor":"Why-do-I-get-No-such-module-FlyHUD-in-my-Xcode-project","type":"heading","text":"Why do I get “No such module ‘FlyHUD’” in my Xcode project?","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Ensure you have:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Added the SPM package dependency correctly","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Added the library product to your target’s “Frameworks, Libraries, and Embedded Content”","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cleaned build folder (Shift+Cmd+K) and rebuilt","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"anchor":"Usage","type":"heading","text":"Usage","level":2},{"anchor":"Why-does-my-HUD-stay-on-screen-forever","type":"heading","text":"Why does my HUD stay on screen forever?","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Every ","type":"text"},{"code":"show()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must be paired with a ","type":"text"},{"code":"hide()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". Common causes:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Forgetting to call ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hide()"},{"text":" on error paths","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hide()"},{"text":" on a different HUD instance","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Using ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isCountEnabled = true"},{"text":" without matching show\/hide pairs","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"Why-does-my-HUD-appear-behind-other-views","type":"heading","text":"Why does my HUD appear behind other views?","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"HUD is added as a subview of the view you specify. Ensure no other views are added","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"after the HUD, or call ","type":"text"},{"code":"view.bringSubviewToFront(hud)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"Why-doesnt-the-keyboard-guide-work","type":"heading","text":"Why doesn’t the keyboard guide work?","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Keyboard guide is iOS-only (not available on tvOS or visionOS)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Ensure ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"HUD.keyboardGuide"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"hud.keyboardGuide"},{"text":" is set to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".center()"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".bottom()"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The keyboard must actually appear (test with a focused text field)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"anchor":"How-do-I-show-HUD-on-the-full-screen-over-navigation-bar","type":"heading","text":"How do I show HUD on the full screen (over navigation bar)?","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Add the HUD to the window instead of the view controller’s view:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["if let window = view.window {","    HUD.show(to: window)","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Can-I-show-multiple-HUDs-simultaneously","type":"heading","text":"Can I show multiple HUDs simultaneously?","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes. Each ","type":"text"},{"code":"HUD.show(to:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" call creates a new HUD instance:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let hud1 = HUD.show(to: view, label: \"Step 1\")","let hud2 = HUD.show(to: view, label: \"Step 2\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"code":"HUD.hideAll(for:)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to dismiss all at once.","type":"text"}]},{"anchor":"How-do-I-update-HUD-content-after-showing","type":"heading","text":"How do I update HUD content after showing?","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Access the HUD’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"contentView","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to update labels, mode, or progress:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let hud = HUD.show(to: view)","\/\/ Later...","hud.contentView.label.text = \"Almost done...\"","hud.contentView.mode = .custom(checkmarkView)"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Appearance","type":"heading","text":"Appearance","level":2},{"anchor":"How-do-I-change-the-HUDs-background-transparency","type":"heading","text":"How do I change the HUD’s background transparency?","level":3},{"code":["\/\/ Content card background","hud.contentView.color = UIColor.black.withAlphaComponent(0.7)","","\/\/ Full-screen overlay","hud.backgroundView.color = UIColor.black.withAlphaComponent(0.3)","hud.backgroundView.style = .solidColor"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"How-do-I-make-the-HUD-largersmaller","type":"heading","text":"How do I make the HUD larger\/smaller?","level":3},{"code":["\/\/ Set minimum size","hud.contentView.layout.minSize = CGSize(width: 150, height: 150)","","\/\/ Or adjust margins","hud.contentView.layout.hMargin = 30","hud.contentView.layout.vMargin = 30"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Can-I-use-SF-Symbols-as-custom-views","type":"heading","text":"Can I use SF Symbols as custom views?","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Yes:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["let config = UIImage.SymbolConfiguration(pointSize: 30, weight: .medium)","let image = UIImage(systemName: \"wifi.exclamationmark\", withConfiguration: config)","let imageView = UIImageView(image: image)","HUD.showStatus(to: view, mode: .custom(imageView), label: \"No Connection\")"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Threading","type":"heading","text":"Threading","level":2},{"anchor":"Is-FlyHUD-thread-safe","type":"heading","text":"Is FlyHUD thread-safe?","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All HUD APIs must be called on the main thread. The library uses ","type":"text"},{"code":"@MainActor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" isolation","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and debug assertions to enforce this. Background work should dispatch to main before","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"interacting with HUD:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["DispatchQueue.global().async {","    let result = heavyComputation()","    DispatchQueue.main.async {","        hud.contentView.label.text = result","        hud.hide()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"anchor":"Migration","type":"heading","text":"Migration","level":2},{"anchor":"How-do-I-migrate-from-MBProgressHUD","type":"heading","text":"How do I migrate from MBProgressHUD?","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"FlyHUD is inspired by MBProgressHUD with a modernized API:","type":"text"}]},{"header":"row","type":"table","rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"MB